..TEXT:
|qua gi@u~: These words (repeated in vs. 20)
register Virgil's sense of return now to the dark place that is
his eternal abode, even as his pallor bears witness to the com
passion he feels for those who share his fate.i
..TEXT:
|cieco mondo~: Hell is "blind" or dark, in both a physical and
a spiritual sense.
