..TEXT:
|peccaro~ = ^peccarono.~  Virgil's affirmation regards only
personal sin, not original sin.  Here, as elsewhere in the poem, it
will be noted that Virgil's understanding of a specifically Christian
truth -- even one such as this, by which he himself is judged -- is
veiled and dim.
