..TEXT:
|O per altrui~: "Altrui" is a possessive here.  With
this turn of phrase, the question evidently concerns the souls of
children who died before they reached the age of responsibility
and personal choice (a matter treated at some length in ^Par.~
XXXII, 40-84).  Only the souls of those "infanti" who had merit,
either through the faith of their parents or through circumcision
or through baptism, were taken from Limbo.
..TCHR:
413
