..TEXT:
|Omero~: Homer.  Dante did not know Greek and had no
direct knowledge of Homer, since no complete or direct
translation of Homer's works existed in the Middle Ages.  The
^Iliad~ and the ^Odyssey~ were known only through quotations by
classical authors and by way of a narrative on the Trojan War in
Latin verse, known variously as ^Homerus Latinus, Homerus
minor~, or ^Pindarus Thebanus~ (supposedly a translation by
Pindar of the ^Iliad~).  See E. Moore (1896), pp. 164-66; P.
Toynbee (1902), pp. 204-15.
