|Diascoride~: Pronounced ^Diasc@oride.~
..TEXT:
|Orfeo~: Orpheus was the mythical Greek poet who, according to
the legend, played so divinely on the lyre given him by Apollo that he
charmed not only the wild beasts, but even the trees and rocks on
Olympus so that they moved from their places and followed him.  Dante's
probable source for Orpheus is Ovid (see ^Metam.~ XI, 1-66).
..TCHR:
